OL,3,CThe war in the Gulf Britain can't
OL,4,Cescape
OL,6,F"We obviously recognise that the
OL,7,Fwholesale price is increasing,"
OL,8,FMichael Shanks, the Energy Minister,
OL,9,Ftold ITV News, "but everybody has a
OL,10,Frole to play in keeping costs as low
OL,11,Fas possible, because every single
OL,12,Fpenny on bills makes a difference."
OL,14,FThe conflict in the Middle East is
OL,15,Fcreating winners and losers.
OL,17,FCountries like the UK - which depend
OL,18,Fheavily on imported energy - are
OL,19,Fparticularly exposed.
OL,21,FRussia is having rather a good war.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@_O]qD@POUtD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
